1926;;High Steppers;;American;;Edwin Carewe;;Mary Astor, Lloyd Hughes, Dolores del RÃ­o;;drama;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/High_Steppers;;Julian Perryam (Lloyd Hughes) gets thrown out of Oxford University and returns to the family estate outside London. He discovers that his sister and his mother are caught up in the "jazz" life and their father, who's the editor of a tabloid scandal rag, is too busy to notice. He also discovers that his sister is in love with the scoundrel son of his father's publisher, Victor Buckland. Learning that Buckland is actually an embezzler, Julian gets a job as a reporter on a muckraking publication and sets out to expose Buckland.